The Gol Gumbaz (Bijapur)
	Deccani style of Indo-Islamic Architecture
	Bijapur, Karnataka
	mausoleum of Muhammad Adil Shah (1626-1656) of the Adil Shahi dynasty of Bijapur (1489-1686)
	a fine convergence of many styles located in medieval India
	Monumentality, majesty and grandeur, integral aspects of the architectural experience in India, are associated with buildings of Bijapur
	While its structural particularities of dome, arches, geometric proportions and load bearing techniques suggest Timurid and Persian styles, it is made of local material and is decorated with surface embellishments popular in the Deccan.
	Four towers at the corners are reminiscent of turrets attached to mosques such as the Puranila Qila in Delhi.